msgid "Etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "But this is peaceful and sublime, namely "

msgctxt "mn152:5.6"
msgid "upekkhā’ti. "
msgstr "equanimity.’ "

msgctxt "mn152:5.7"
msgid "Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati; "
msgstr "Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in them cease, "

msgctxt "mn152:5.8"
msgid "upekkhā saṇṭhāti. "
msgstr "and equanimity becomes stabilized. "

#. VAR: accharaṃ → accharikaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn152:5.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso appakasireneva accharaṃ pahareyya; "
msgstr "It’s like how a strong person can effortlessly snap their fingers. "

msgctxt "mn152:5.10"
msgid "evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr "Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized. "

msgctxt "mn152:5.11"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā sotaviññeyyesu saddesu. "
msgstr "In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding sounds known by the ear. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, pts-vp-pli3.300, sc5
msgctxt "mn152:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "Furthermore, when a mendicant smells an odor with their nose, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them. "

