msgstr "and equanimity becomes stabilized. "

#. VAR: vameyya → vammeyya (s1-3) | sandhameyya (mr)
msgctxt "mn152:7.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso jivhagge kheḷapiṇḍaṃ saṃyūhitvā appakasirena vameyya; "
msgstr "It’s like how a strong person who’s formed a glob of spit on the tip of their tongue could easily spit it out. "

msgctxt "mn152:7.10"
msgid "evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr "Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized. "

msgctxt "mn152:7.11"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu. "
msgstr "In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding tastes known by the tongue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, sc7
msgctxt "mn152:8.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "Furthermore, when a mendicant feels a touch with their body, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them. "

msgctxt "mn152:8.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

