msgid "ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā kāyaviññeyyesu phoṭṭhabbesu. "
msgstr "In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding touches known by the body. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc8
msgctxt "mn152:9.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "Furthermore, when a mendicant knows a thought with their mind, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them. "

msgctxt "mn152:9.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "mn152:9.3"
msgid "‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me. "

msgctxt "mn152:9.4"
msgid "Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated. "

