msgstr "and equanimity becomes stabilized. "

msgctxt "mn152:9.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso divasaṃsantatte ayokaṭāhe dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni nipāteyya. "
msgstr "It’s like how a strong person could let two or three drops of water fall onto an iron cauldron that had been heated all day. "

msgctxt "mn152:9.10"
msgid "Dandho, ānanda, udakaphusitānaṃ nipāto, atha kho naṃ khippameva parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya; "
msgstr "The drops would be slow to fall, but they’d quickly dry up and evaporate. "

msgctxt "mn152:9.11"
msgid "evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr "Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized. "

msgctxt "mn152:9.12"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā manoviññeyyesu dhammesu. "
msgstr "In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding thoughts known by the mind. "

msgctxt "mn152:9.13"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how there is the supreme development of the faculties in the training of the noble one. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, pts-vp-pli3.301, sc9
msgctxt "mn152:10.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, sekho hoti pāṭipado? "
msgstr "And how are they a practicing trainee? "

msgctxt "mn152:10.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them. "

msgctxt "mn152:10.3"
msgid "So tena uppannena manāpena uppannena amanāpena uppannena manāpāmanāpena aṭṭīyati harāyati jigucchati. "
msgstr "They are horrified, repelled, and disgusted by that. "

msgctxt "mn152:10.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears … "

msgctxt "mn152:10.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … "
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

msgctxt "mn152:10.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … "
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

msgctxt "mn152:10.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … "
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

msgctxt "mn152:10.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "When they know a thought with their mind, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them. "

msgctxt "mn152:10.9"
msgid "So tena uppannena manāpena uppannena amanāpena uppannena manāpāmanāpena aṭṭīyati harāyati jigucchati. "
msgstr "They are horrified, repelled, and disgusted by that. "

msgctxt "mn152:10.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, sekho hoti pāṭipado. "
msgstr "That’s how they are a practicing trainee. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11-15, sc10
msgctxt "mn152:11-15.1"
msgid "Kathañcānanda, ariyo hoti bhāvitindriyo? "
msgstr "And how are they a noble one with developed faculties? "

msgctxt "mn152:11-15.2"
msgid "Idhānanda, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them. "

#. VAR: paṭikūle → paṭikkūle (sabbattha)
msgctxt "mn152:11-15.3"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:11-15.4"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:11-15.5"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:11-15.6"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive and the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:11-15.7"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako tattha viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16, pts-vp-pli3.302, sc11
msgctxt "mn152:16.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ear … "

msgctxt "mn152:16.2"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … "
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

msgctxt "mn152:16.3"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … "
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

msgctxt "mn152:16.4"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … "
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

msgctxt "mn152:16.5"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ. "
msgstr "When they know a thought with their mind, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them. "

msgctxt "mn152:16.6"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:16.7"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:16.8"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:16.9"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive and the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:16.10"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayampi abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako tattha viharati sato sampajāno. "
msgstr "If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "mn152:16.11"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, ariyo hoti bhāvitindriyo. "
msgstr "That’s how they are a noble one with developed faculties. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, sc12
msgctxt "mn152:17.1"
msgid "Iti kho, ānanda, desitā mayā ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā, desito sekho pāṭipado, desito ariyo bhāvitindriyo. "
msgstr "So, Ānanda, I have taught the supreme development of the faculties in the training of the noble one, I have taught the practicing trainee, and I have taught the noble one with developed faculties. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18
msgctxt "mn152:18.1"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, ānanda, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā. "
msgstr "Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples. "

msgctxt "mn152:18.2"
msgid "Etāni, ānanda, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni, jhāyathānanda, mā pamādattha, mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti. "
msgstr "Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, Ānanda! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "mn152:18.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn152:18.4"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn152:18.5"
msgid "Indriyabhāvanāsuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "mn152:18.6"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavaggo niṭṭhito pañcamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn152:18.7"
msgid "Anāthapiṇḍiko channo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn152:18.8"
msgid "puṇṇo nandakarāhulā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn152:18.9"
msgid "Chachakkaṃ saḷāyatanikaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn152:18.10"
msgid "nagaravindeyyasuddhikā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn152:18.11"
msgid "Indriyabhāvanā cāpi, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn152:18.12"
msgid "vaggo ovādapañcamoti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><blockquote class="vagguddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "mn152:18.13"
msgid "Devadahonupado ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn152:18.14"
msgid "Suññato ca vibhaṅgako; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn152:18.15"
msgid "Saḷāyatanoti vaggā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn152:18.16"
msgid "Uparipaṇṇāsake ṭhitāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "mn152:18.17"
msgid "Uparipaṇṇāsakaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn152:18.18"
msgid "Tīhi paṇṇāsakehi paṭimaṇḍito sakalo "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "mn152:18.19"
msgid "majjhimanikāyo samatto. "
msgstr "The Middle Discourses is completed."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
